post_text:
Dear Parents, Students, and NUSD Community:

Wishing that everyone is safe and healthy at this time!

NUSD would like to thank and appreciate our parents/grandparents and students for all their patience, understanding, positive feedback, and being mindful that NUSD will continue to prioritize the safety, security, and health of all our school communities. All recommendations and determinations for Reopening Schools for In-person Instruction/Hybrid Model in the Fall will be based on the data/benchmark positivity rates.

As per the most current data/benchmark; For the past two weeks, Santa Cruz County has not met the benchmark below positive test rate of 7%.

Therefore, NUSD will continue with the Online Instruction Program until further notice.

Please follow the safety guidelines, wear a mask when out in public and around other people, wash your hands often, and practice social (physical) distance avoiding large gatherings.

Be personally responsible and stay at home as much as possible........

Thank you and Be Safe!

Superintendent Parra

ESTUDIANTES, PADRES Y COMUNIDAD ESCOLAR DEL NUSD:

Hemos recibido un informe de nuestro representante de T-Mobile que ha identificado el problema cuando los estudiantes y profesores son expulsados de cualquier aplicación relacionada con Google. Este es un problema a nivel nacional y lo han elevado a la máxima prioridad. Ayer hicieron los cambios necesarios en sus sistemas y se han enviado a todos sus servicios de red.
Le recomendamos que reinicie el dispositivo quitando la batería del Mifi y luego colocándola de nuevo y reiniciando el dispositivo. Esto restablecerá el servicio de red en el Mifi y tomará la nueva configuración lanzada por T-Mobile. Confían en que esto evitará que los usuarios sean expulsados de sus sesiones. Este problema no está relacionado con la vista de cuadrícula de Google para Meet.

¡Gracias!

post_text:
NUSD STUDENTS, PARENTS AND SCHOOL COMMUNITY:

We have received a report from our T-Mobile representative that they have identified the issue when students and teachers get kicked out of any Google related applications. This is a nationwide issue and they have escalated this matter to top priority. They made the necessary changes on their systems yesterday and is been pushed out to all their network services.
We advise you to restart the device by removing the battery on the Mifi and then placing it back and restarting the device. This will reset the network service on the Mifi and will grab the new configuration pushed out by T-Mobile. They are confident that this will correct users from being kicked out of their sessions. This issue is not related to the Google grid view for Meet.

Thank you!

Buenas tardes: como padres de estudiantes de NUSD inscritos para el año escolar 2020-2021, están invitados a completar una encuesta. Como saben, la escuela comenzará en línea para todos los estudiantes el 5 de agosto de 2020. Cuando sea permitido asistir a la escuela en persona, más adelante en el semestre; todos los padres tendrán la opción de: 1) Que su hijo/a continúe trabajando en línea. 2) Hacer una transición a un modelo híbrido (siendo este en línea y en persona). Y por último 3) Una transición de instrucción en persona.

Ayúdenos a planificar el año escolar completando esta encuesta. Sus comentarios son importantes y nos permitirán planificar adecuadamente la instrucción de su hijo/a. Haga clic en el enlace a continuación para comenzar la encuesta:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSensGt3DK_I9gKAMA2CA_DUYYseIiGNgzig6a5hLKOxoD3jEQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

post_text:
Good afternoon--

As parents of NUSD students enrolled for the 2020-2021 school year, you are invited to complete a survey. As you know, school will begin online for all students on Aug. 5, 2020. If and when school is permitted to occur in-person, later during the fall semester, all parents will have the option of 1) having their child remain working online, 2) transitioning to a hybrid model (both online and in-person), or 3) transitioning to in-person instruction.

Please assist us in planning for school by completing this survey to select the model you will want for your child when in-person instruction can safely begin. Your feedback is important and will enable us to plan appropriately for your child's instruction. Click on the link below to begin the survey:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSensGt3DK_I9gKAMA2CA_DUYYseIiGNgzig6a5hLKOxoD3jEQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

post_text:
Over 800 students participated in the free Nogales Unified School District summer school programs that were offered over the past two months through various platforms. NUSD offered summer school through Edgenuity, its own NUSD online program with a wide variety of courses from May 24 through June 24. We had a staggering 437 students take advantage of this program.

NUSD also partnered with Arizona State University through ASU Digital Prep and their “open scale” courses. ASU opened up the majority of their summer school courses to NUSD students which, including “open scale courses”were free of charge. NHS students who took advantage of these opportunities not only received high school credit, but they also were able to receive college credit in many of the courses as well. The partnerships formed between NUSD and ASU allowed 473 students to take advantage of these online courses for free.

La distribución del producto se llevará a cabo en el estacionamiento de estudiantes de la Nogales High School a partir de las 9:00 a.m. del jueves 16 de abril.

Se proporcionará un paquete completo de productos y se colocará en su vehículo.

¡Gracias!

Superintendente Parra
